  "elapsed_s": 6.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] In 1943, [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] Father received a note from the [GERMAN], the famous Aryanization authority in Berlin, that they wanted to see him.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] German patriot as he was, and also, I think, accustomed to follow authority, took the next train to Berlin, where he was instantly arrested.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "He ended up, for reasons that I don't know, in a prison in Vienna [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] and was apparently during that time [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] threatened with-- sort of daily-- with being taken from the prison to Mathausen, which was the prime death factory among the Austrian concentration camps.",
      "word_count": 52
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It was actually a-- a quarry, like Buchenwald.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Well, anyway, so he was in prison.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And then the next thing we knew-- well, we knew he was in prison really from our contact in Vienna, which was, again, General [INAUDIBLE].",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So then one day, maybe eight weeks after he disappeared, [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] Father was back.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And what apparently had happened is that his right-wing, monarchist friends in the army had managed to get him out of prison and assigned a German soldier to him, to walk through the woods from Slovakia into Hungary.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] And then at the next train station he took the train, and there he was.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Well, my conjecture-- well, very soon after that time, suitcases of British pounds-- he used to white British pound notes, and I don't know whether that was 20 pounds or 100 pounds or what-- arrived in our-- in our apartment in Buda.",
      "word_count": 42
    }
  ],
